<p>Review the calendar every Friday. Move published rows to Status "Published" and pull the next row up the queue. The template is now a living system, not a static file.</p>
<p><strong>Why this step matters:</strong> Research without a shipping schedule is a very detailed way to do nothing. The calendar tab converts a 3,000-row research universe into a weekly publish cadence the team can actually execute. This is the step where rankings start to arrive 4 to 6 months later.</p>
<p><strong>Checklist for Step 8:</strong></p>
